<number id="3DC6FC7DFFB6C05186CCF955BE70F935" box="[215,287,1714,1739]" pageId="7" pageNumber="535" value="53.0" valueMax="56.0" valueMin="50.0">50–56</number>
</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB6C051868CF91DBB0DF8ED" blockId="7.[151,1436,1786,2027]" box="[151,1122,1786,1811]" pageId="7" pageNumber="535">Creamy white. Vertex with submarginal brown stripe either side of mid-line anteriorly.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C314BDD1FFB6C05186DCF8F9BFBFF815" pageId="7" pageNumber="535" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB6C05186DCF8F9BB23F85D" blockId="7.[151,1436,1786,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB6C05186DCF8F9BE13F8C8" box="[199,380,1822,1846]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="535">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer caudo-ventrally rounded with tooth-like short process. Subgenital plate with emargination on lateral margin near apex. Style with prominent subapical lobe, apophysis slender, strongly laterally curved. Aedeagal shaft elongate, membranous except for a narrow dorsal sclerotized rod; preatrial processes bladelike, with ventral margin expanded subapically and strongly serrated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB6C05186DCF848BFBFF815" blockId="7.[151,1436,1786,2027]" pageId="7" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB6C05186DCF848BE1EF838" box="[199,369,1967,1990]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="535">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male 4.0 mm long and 
<quantity id="4CF643BFFFB6C0518460F848BDBEF838" box="[635,721,1967,1991]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="535" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes. Female 
<quantity id="4CF643BFFFB6C05185E2F848BB20F838" box="[1017,1103,1967,1991]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="535" unit="mm" value="4.2">4.2 mm</quantity>
long and 1.0 mm wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
