<subSubSection id="C314BDD1FFB9C05E86DCF90EBAE6F8DA" pageId="8" pageNumber="536" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB1EE5AFFB9C05E86DCF90EBAE6F8DA" blockId="8.[151,1436,1700,1829]" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB9C05E86DCF90EBE54F8FC" bold="true" box="[199,315,1769,1794]" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E95D9FFB9C05E8446F90DBD9DF8FC" box="[605,754,1770,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nicolaus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bihamatus">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB9C05E8446F90DBD1FF8FF" box="[605,624,1770,1793]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB9C05E8466F90DBD9DF8FC" box="[637,754,1770,1794]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">bihamatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but its aedeagal shaft is broader in ventral view and preatrial processes are subapically expanded with strongly serrated ventral margin. See also Remarks under 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E95D9FFB9C05E82F7F8EABAEDF8DB" box="[1260,1410,1805,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nicolaus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="536" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bihamatus">
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB9C05E82F7F8EABB90F8DA" box="[1260,1279,1805,1828]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">N</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B97A3248FFB9C05E8316F8EABAEDF8DB" box="[1293,1410,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="536">bihamatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
